OL,3,CCharities warn of record child poverty
OL,4,Cif two-child benefit cap not scrapped
OL,6,F"If it is not scrapped, the stark
OL,7,Freality is that child poverty will be
OL,8,Fsignificantly higher at the end of
OL,9,Fthis parliament than when the
OL,10,Fgovernment took office, making this
OL,11,Fthe first time a Labour government
OL,12,Fwould leave such a legacy, and the
OL,13,Fnumber of children living in poverty
OL,14,Fwill be at its highest since records
OL,15,Fbegan."
